There are several other GBA emulators for Android, but GBA.emu is the only one I've used that is perfect in nearly every way. Full, 100% compatibility with all my games, customizable controls, hell, even an option to sync a Wii remote to the device. The only thing it's missing is cheats, not that I use them. Worth every penny.

Two qualms:   First, if I select the landscape or portrait views under options, all that does is make the GBA.emu menus go into landscape or portrait. The actual emulated game does whatever the orientation on my phone is. I'd like it to remain landscape 100% of the time, but currently that isn't possible.  Second, there is no Gameshark or ActionReplay support. I wanna be able to have all the starters in Pokemon Emerald! This one isn't as important to me.  I docked a star for each of these major issues.
replyContent:
There's a separate orientation option for the GUI and in-game, set it under Options -> Video to affect in-game. (This info is accurate as of version 1.5.10 and older)

Full cheat code support will be added in version 1.5.11.

content: Easily the best GameBoy Advance emulator for Android, if ActionReplay/GameShark support is added it would be a 5.
replyContent: Full cheat code support will be added in version 1.5.11.

This emulator has been very smooth for me and the sound quality is perfect compared to other android emulators. After you load a game, the user interface itself by default can be accessed by tapping top-right corner. The menu is looking good and there are plenty options to choose from. The on-screen button properties can be edited in various ways with prepared values, all you need to do is to select one and check which one suits your needs the most. Although most of the games run perfectly, I've been trying to run Golden Sun and Golden Sun 2 and I found that everything goes perfect until you will get into the battle scene. The battle background becomes distorted and the characters and enemies are messed up or completely invisible. However the sound effects and music itself are perfect, which happens to be working properly only with this emulator. If not for that issue, It would be first android emulator to play golden sun 1/2 so smoothly without distorted sound. UPDATE: the newest version has fixed graphics,  therefore you can finally play Golden Sun 1/2 in it's full light without changing anything. Amazing! Totally worth the money.
